                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>6</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="199149" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 13 Jun 2017 23:06:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9633&quot; title=&quot;Add kernel-doc style comments to All lustre Code describing function &amp;amp; parameters.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9633&quot;&gt;LU-9633&lt;/a&gt; is better set up to handle this&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="177217" author="sguminsx" created="Fri, 9 Dec 2016 12:06:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds good, Peter.  Andreas sent me a few other higher priority tickets to work, but I&apos;ll keep this on my queue and get to it once I&apos;ve finished with those.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="177155" author="pjones" created="Thu, 8 Dec 2016 22:36:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that it is ok for Steve to own this for now, even if it is not his top priority&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="177042" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 8 Dec 2016 14:00:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not the highest priority. Currently I&apos;m busy with other syncing work. I opened the ticket just to make a note this work needs to be done at some time in the future. Also I like to point out if new comments are added to the lustre kernel source it would be preferable to use this new api.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="177010" author="adilger" created="Thu, 8 Dec 2016 08:23:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James, is this really a priority?&#160; I doubt there is much demand for this change to be done before moving the Lustre client out of staging, and if anything I&apos;d prefer effort to be spent on writing &lt;b&gt;new&lt;/b&gt; comments for code that is missing it, or improving the man pages (e.g. &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7648&quot; title=&quot;split lctl lfsck sub-commands to new man pages&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7648&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7648&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) rather than spending time and effort to reformat existing comments to meet some new formatting style.&#160; The comment reformatting benefits almost nobody.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="176969" author="simmonsja" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 22:13:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, glad to help&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="176965" author="sguminsx" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 21:59:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, I&apos;ll start diving into it tomorrow morning.  James, I might have a few questions, so I&apos;d appreciate your continued help.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="176964" author="pjones" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 21:48:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ok then let&apos;s find someone else to help&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steve&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please assist with this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="176961" author="simmonsja" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 21:38:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can but it might be a bit before I get to it since I have a lot on my plate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="176956" author="pjones" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 21:16:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Are you planning on doing this work James?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
